rder of the question. Taking the previous example, some dialects of English would say “He doesn’t know what time is it”. %0a%3c %0a%3c One thing to note about embedded question inversion is that a complementizer, such as if or whether, is not allowed when a question exhibits inversion. For example, consider the Standard American sentence “He’s wondering whether the test is today.” The inverted sentence “He’s wondering is the test today” is acceptable, but the sentence “He’s wondering whether is the test today” is not because a complementizer and inversion cannot occur in the same sentence. %0a%3c %0a%3c Source: https://ygdp.yale.edu/phenomena/inversion-embedded-questions %0a%3c  %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Expansions:%0a%3c [[#expansions]]%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#expansionsend]]%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c %25red%25 '''Add an expansion:'''%0a%3c %0a%3c (:if [ exists GradebookExpansions.{$Name}-{$Author} || equal {$Author} {$:Author} ] :)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:else:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#newexpansion:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:ifend:)%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Comments%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c (:section: A:)%0a%3c (:Category: MorphosyntacticDiversity:)%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
